    "result": {"data":{"markdownRemark":{"excerpt":"Hi Friends üëã, Welcome To aGuideHub!  To change color of mui badge in react js, you can use this code . This will change color of mui badge in React JS. Today‚Ä¶","html":"<p>Hi Friends üëã,</p>\n<p>Welcome To aGuideHub! </p>\n<p>To change color of mui badge in react js, you can use this code <code class=\"language-text\">color: \"blue\"</code>. This will change color of mui badge in React JS.</p>\n<p>Today, I am going to show you, How to change color of mui badge in react js.</p>\n<h2>Installation</h2>\n<p>Install the following packages to use mui Badge in react js.</p>\n<p><code class=\"language-text\">npm</code></p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\">npm install @mui<span class=\"token operator\">/</span>material @emotion<span class=\"token operator\">/</span>react @emotion<span class=\"token operator\">/</span>styled</code></pre></div>\n<p><code class=\"language-text\">yarn</code></p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\">yarn add @mui<span class=\"token operator\">/</span>material @emotion<span class=\"token operator\">/</span>react @emotion<span class=\"token operator\">/</span>styled</code></pre></div>\n<p>Table of contents</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Install MUI and create a new React app.</li>\n<li>Import Material-UI Badge.</li>\n<li>Use the Badge Component</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Step 1: Install MUI and create a new React app.</h3>\n<p>First you have to install the React project. You should use <code class=\"language-text\">create-react-app</code> command to create a new React project.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\">npx create<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>react<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>app my<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>app\ncd my<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>app\nnpm start</code></pre></div>\n<h3>Step 2: Import Material-UI Badge.</h3>\n<p>After installing <code class=\"language-text\">MUI</code>, you have to import your React component. To do this, add the following line to the top of your component file.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> React <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"react\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> Badge <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"@mui/material/Badge\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code></pre></div>\n<h3>Step 3: Use the Badge Component</h3>\n<p>You can use the <code class=\"language-text\">Badge</code> component in your react js. For example, The Badge component is used to display importan notifications. You can use <code class=\"language-text\">&lt;StyledBadge></code> component make a Badge box in react js.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>StyledBadge badgeContent<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span><span class=\"token number\">5</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span><span class=\"token comment\">/* Your component or content here */</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n<span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>StyledBadge<span class=\"token operator\">></span></code></pre></div>\n<h2>MUI material change color of mui badge example.</h2>\n<p>The below code is an example, to do custom of mui Badge, you need to import <code class=\"language-text\">Badge</code> Component. you can use this mui styles <code class=\"language-text\">&lt;StyledBadge></code> and to change color of mui badge in react js.</p>\n<p><code class=\"language-text\">App.js</code></p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> React <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"react\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> Badge <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"@mui/material/Badge\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span> withStyles <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"@mui/styles\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> StyledBadge <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token function\">withStyles</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token parameter\">theme</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=></span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token literal-property property\">badge</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token literal-property property\">backgroundColor</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"red\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n    <span class=\"token literal-property property\">color</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"blue\"</span> <span class=\"token comment\">// Change the text color as needed</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>Badge<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> <span class=\"token function-variable function\">App</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=></span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">return</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>\n    <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>div<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n      <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>StyledBadge badgeContent<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span><span class=\"token number\">5</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n        <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span><span class=\"token comment\">/* Your component or content here */</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n      <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>StyledBadge<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n    <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>div<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">export</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">default</span> App<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>In the above code example, I have used the <code class=\"language-text\">@mui/material</code> component and changed color of mui badge in react js.</p>\n<p>Check the output of the above code example.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 311px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/cb98778720cc437fd6ddf98f7fc530bc/c6a73/change-color-of-mui-badge.webp\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 53.79746835443038%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/webp;base64,UklGRlIAAABXRUJQVlA4IEYAAACQAwCdASoUAAsAPtFUpEuoJKOhsAgBABoJQBOj+ABgb3YMeNFgAPZHvKPNPWWbgLeDACVeRct5Jyb3SWQYB90nVlvi7QAA'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"React, Mui, change, icon\"\n        title=\"React, Mui, change, icon\"\n        src=\"/static/cb98778720cc437fd6ddf98f7fc530bc/c6a73/change-color-of-mui-badge.webp\"\n        srcset=\"/static/cb98778720cc437fd6ddf98f7fc530bc/81b7c/change-color-of-mui-badge.webp 158w,\n/static/cb98778720cc437fd6ddf98f7fc530bc/c6a73/change-color-of-mui-badge.webp 311w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 311px) 100vw, 311px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>Here, we are provided code sandbox links for the above program change color of mui badge in react js. Then you can use whenever you want and do the changes as per your requirements.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://aguidehub.com/codesandbox/?code=cocky-scott-yn89kg\" rel=\"nofollow\"  target=\"_BLANK\" >Try it Yourself</a></p>\n<p>All the best üëç</p>","frontmatter":{"title":"How to change color of mui badge in react js?","tags":["React"],"date":"June 28, 2023","description":"Example of change color of mui badge in React js with step by step tutorial - aGuideHub","social_image":"media/template/reactjs.jpg"}},"prev":null,"next":{"